io.amelia.support

Class Voluntary<Type>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.amelia.support.Voluntary<Type>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    VoluntaryWithCause

    public class Voluntary<Type>
extends java.lang.Object
    An expanded container object which may or may not contain a non-null value and/or exception, is similar to Optional but adds error handling. If a value is present, isPresent() will return true and get() will return the value. If a cause is present, hasErrored() will return true and getException() will return the cause.

    Additional methods that depend on the presence or absence of a contained value are provided, such as orElse() (return a default value if value not present) and ifPresent() (execute a block of code if the value is present).

    Additional methods for interfacing with Java 8 features are also present, such as of(Optional). Methods ending with "compatible" are intended in mimic the logic of similar methods found in Optional, e.g., flatMapCompatible(FunctionWithException)

    See Also:
    Optional
